<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-3560] Detect uncaught exceptions in UoWProcessor to ensure UoW is done even for those uncaught exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3560</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Camel routing engines will handle this in 99.9% of the cases, but when you shutdown a Spring AC then Spring may stop beans in whatever order and this can cause those beans to fail operating during a graceful shutdown. And in worst case exceptions is thrown in situations where they are not normally done.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To cater for that and other situations the UoWProcessor should detect this and act accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ensure the in flight registry will be tracked and we are not stuck with a missing inflight message, causing Camel to wait for the 300 sec timeout to shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example just try hitting ctrl + c in that camel-example-management and you can see such an example.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
